-- Turkish Lira Weakens First Time in Four Days, Bond Yields Rise
-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 2012-08-07T08:01:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/turkish-lira-weakens-first-time-in-four-days-bond-yields-rise.html
The Turkish lira weakened for the
first time in four days and bond yields rose for a second day.  The lira weakened 0.2 percent to 1.7792 per dollar at 10:49
a.m. in Istanbul. Yields on benchmark two-year bonds rose one
basis point, or 0.01 percentage point, to 7.54 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcuk Gokoluk in Istanbul at 
